thread.title_full: Squalicum football holds at No. 4, Baker drops

author: The Bellingham Herald
title: Squalicum football holds at No. 4, Baker drops
text:
October 7, 2015 Squalicum football holds at No. 4, Baker drops Squalicum’s Riley Zehnder hits Burlington-Edison QB Hunter Anderson after a pass during a NWC game Friday, Oct. 2, in Burlington. Evan Abell The Bellingham Herald i Order Reprint of this Story 
The Squalicum High School football team stayed at No. 4 in the latest Class 2A Associated Press Washington State Football Poll, but now the Storm holds fourth alone instead of being tied with Hockinson, which dropped to No. 5. 
The Storm improved to 5-0 after a 54-31 Northwest Conference win over Burlington-Edison (3-2), which dropped from No. 8 to No. 10. 
Mount Baker (4-1) dropped from No. 5 to No. 7 in the Class 1A poll despite a 33-28 win over Meridian. 
Ferndale (4-1) received votes in the Class 3A poll but couldn’t crack the Top 10. Washington Football Prep Poll
